Description: Streptococcus pneumoniae partial 23S rRNA gene, strain 547.
Organism : Streptococcus pneumoniae
Accession Number : AM180136.1

Streptococcus pneumoniae is a gram-positive bacterium.
It is responsible for causing pneumococcal infections such as community-acquired pneumonia, bacterial meningitis, bacteremia, otitis media, sinusitis, septic arthritis, osteomyelitis, peritonitis, and endocarditis.
